==English==
===Etymology===
From [[dull]] + [[-ville]], evoking a (fictional) town.

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|Dullsville}}
'''dullsville'''
#A [[fictional]] or [[generic]] location that is [[boring]] or [[dull]].
#A state or condition of [[boredom]] or [[disinterest]].
#:''You can proceed with the same monotonous routine and live in '''dullsville''' forever, or you can think of something new.''

